<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="suggest-vt">suggest <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /sə'dʒest/    美 /sə'dʒest/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>建议；提议；提出：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>John suggested a swim and we all agreed. 
约翰提议去游泳，我们都同意了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>suggest doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He suggested playing football after school. 
他提议放学后去踢足球。</p><footer>译林④ – 2</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>suggest (that) ... (should) do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The doctor suggested he go for a holiday. 
医生建议他去休个假。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We all suggested that a lab be built. 
我们都建议建个实验室。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>it is suggested that sb (should) do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It has been suggested that bright children (should) take their exams early.
有人提议天资好的孩子应该提前考试。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is suggested that we smile as much as possible.
有人建议我们尽可能多地微笑。</p><footer>2010 湖北书面表达</footer></div>

<h3 id="advise-suggest">辨析 advise, suggest</h3>
<p>表示“建议”时，二者意义十分接近。但用法不尽相同。<br />
<strong>advise</strong> 
<strong>suggest</strong> </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>doing sth 
建议做某事</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>that …(should) do sth 
提议…做某事</p></div>

<h4 id="2-recommend">2.★ <strong>推荐(recommend)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Can you suggest a good dictionary? 
你能推荐本好字典吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3indicate">3.<strong>表明；暗示(indicate)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>suggest +(that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her expression suggested (that) she was angry. 
她的表情说明她生气了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you suggesting that I’m not working hard? 
你是在暗示说我工作不努力吗？</p></div>

<p>注: 当suggest意为“建议”时，其后的宾语从句用虚拟语气；当suggest意为“表明；暗示”时， 其后的宾语从句则不用虚拟语气。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Some classmates suggest we can go to places of interest nearby.  （2016 全国 改错）  </li>
<li>Bill suggested <strong><em>_</em></strong>___ (hold) a meeting on what to do for the Shanghai Expo during the vacation.  （2009 上海改）  </li>
<li>He came to my class every week, but his attitude <strong><em>_</em></strong>___ (表明) he was not really interested in the subject.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. 删掉can或者can → should  2. holding   3. suggested / indicated  </p></div>